  "diffSummary": "Reconciliation of the session-restore feature merged in f343624 (code shipped; the contract/evidence were never authored and its smoke needed a live GUI relaunch). command/restore_sessions loads each saved account from the local store, decrypts its credential with the keychain master key, and re-logs-in + re-listens via the shared login_and_listen path, returning the restored profiles; an account whose login fails is marked reauth-needed (store.mark_reauth_needed) and skipped so the others still come online. The frontend (session.svelte.ts restore()) calls restore_sessions at startup behind a loading gate and shows the QR screen only when zero accounts restore. This reconciliation captures the previously-missing live relaunch proof: on launch the core log shows the saved account auto-reconnecting with no QR.",
